"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Mar-06 22:36</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1539e5b0dff9db9cf609ab716b346f9e2f1241f5\">[59094]</a></span>: Debug in-memory state tracking of reused files. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7514\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7514'); return false;\" title=\"Bugfixes and creature comforts for DataReuse\">#7514</a></span> Fixups include better tracking of space usage and when files were last reused.  (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Mar-06 22:36</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/5e19b51c2fd4323fa96bb17407e70bc1823f084b\">[59092]</a></span>: Allow reuse info config to specify prefixes. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7514\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7514'); return false;\" title=\"Bugfixes and creature comforts for DataReuse\">#7514</a></span> With this, an admin can simply set aside multiple GB at a time (also fixes the fact that, since `param_integer` returns a 32-bit integer, we could only set 2.4GB of reuse directory previously!).  (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Mar-06 22:36</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c737013272ba7688c21693e6994adb073d2717e1\">[59091]</a></span>: Refactor `parse_int64_bytes` to be part of utils. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7514\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7514'); return false;\" title=\"Bugfixes and creature comforts for DataReuse\">#7514</a></span> In `submit_utils.cpp`, we had the useful `parse_int64_bytes` function that took a config value and converted it to a `uint64_t` value (correctly handling suffixes like MB, GB). This moves the function from `submit_utils` to `metric_utils` so others\u00a0[...]\n (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Mar-06 22:36</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/eeff232115f828fccb10c0711917416f9c4dc66a\">[59090]</a></span>: Fixup warnings on Mac OS X. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7514\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7514'); return false;\" title=\"Bugfixes and creature comforts for DataReuse\">#7514</a></span> Particularly, it seems that Mac and Linux fight over the right print specifier for `uint64_t`; this simply casts everything to `unsigned long long` across all platforms.  (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2020-May-02 14:51", "status": "resolved", "created": "2020-Feb-20 08:37", "fixed_version": "2020-Feb-20 08:37", "broken_version": "", "priority": "2", "subsystem": "DaemonsExecNode", "assigned_to": "bbockelm", "derived_from": "", "creator": "bbockelm", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "bbockelman@morgridge.org", "due_date": ""}